Project Flow

Is project mein kya-kya hai aur ye kaise kaam karta hai, main easy language mein explain karta hoon (aap ise apne viva ya interview mein bhi bol sakti hain):

1. Real-time Intelligence (The News Engine)
Project ka main kaam hai duniya bhar se "War" aur "Conflict" ki news nikalna.

Kaise kaam karta hai: Humne GNews API ka use kiya hai. Jaise hi dashboard load hota hai, ye API duniya bhar ke news servers se connect karti hai.

Query Logic: Humne search query mein war OR conflict OR military dala hai taaki sirf relevant news hi aaye.

2. Severity Algorithm (The Brain)
Ye project sirf news dikhata nahi hai, balki use analyze bhi karta hai.

High Intensity: Agar title mein "attack", "bomb", ya "military" jaise words hain, toh app use Red label deta hai.

Diplomatic: Agar "peace", "talks", ya "aid" jaise words hain, toh use Blue label milta hai.

Monitoring: Baaki normal news ko monitor state mein rakhta hai.

3. Visual Intelligence (The World Map)
Aapne jo react-simple-maps use kiya hai, wo project ko professional look deta hai.

Global View: Map par Red dots (Markers) dikhate hain ki "Critical Zones" kahan hain.

Interactive Markers: Ye markers animate (pulse) karte hain, jo ek war-room dashboard wali feel dete hain.

4. Data Analytics (The Charts)
Humne Recharts library use ki hai taaki data sirf list mein na dikhe, balki graphical format mein bhi ho.

Pie Chart: Ye dikhata hai ki total news mein se kitne percent news "High Intensity" wali hain.

Bar Chart: Ye severity levels ka comparison dikhata hai.

5. Secure Vault (LocalStorage Persistence)
Ye ek professional feature hai jisme user intelligence reports ko "Save" kar sakta hai.

Logic: Jab aap "Save" button par click karti hain, toh wo report browser ke localStorage mein save ho jati hai.

Benefit: Agar aap page refresh bhi karein, toh aapka "Vault" khali nahi hoga. Ye data browser mein encrypted format (JSON string) mein rehta hai.

6. UI/UX (Cyber-Security Theme)
Project ka design "Military Grade" theme par based hai:

Tailwind CSS: Dark mode (bg-[#020617]), neon borders, aur monochromatic fonts ka use kiya gaya hai.

Ticker: Upar ek moving news ticker hai jo live update ki feel deta hai.

Toaster Alerts: react-hot-toast ka use kiya hai critical alerts dikhane ke liye.

Tech Stack Summary:

Frontend: React (Vite)
Styling: Tailwind CSS
Charts: Recharts
Maps: React-simple-maps
API: GNews API
Notifications: React Hot Toast